race.comment: ATELIER (4) has transferred from the Archibald to Lees stable and returns from a three-month spell. In the money at both previous first-up runs. Talented mare who was beaten just 1.5 lengths in a Canberra Guineas at three, so she has the class to win a race like this. CAN'T TOUCH THIS (7) made it two wins from her last three outings when she led from barrier rise and just lasted over 1200m at Gosford last time. New to this distance and draws off the track so it gets tougher, but she is going better than ever and must be respected. HOW MUCH BETTER (2) came from well back with a mighty finish but missed picking up CAN'T TOUCH THIS by a whisker when resuming at Gosford recently. Big chance to turn the tables over an extra 150m today. AROHA STONE (5) makes her return today after an 18-week spell. Raced well in town last prep on wet tracks but is adept in all going. Recent trial winner who is all set for a bright start to the prep. TAVOLO (8) is rarely far away - one for the exotics.
